  "description": "<h2 id=\"introduction\">Introduction</h2>\n<p>A short trip with beautiful views. Not really a canyon, but a couple\n+100' rappels down a wall. Best combined with Angels Landing for those\nseeking a medium day of adventure where you can get a little later start\nor have an afternoon finish.</p>\n<p>The canyon is on the same approach/exit to Angels Landing. If\ncombining, drop all vertical gear at the drop in; stowing out of sight\nof the hiking trail and passing visitors. Continue on the trail to\nsummit Angels Landing and return to the drop in, completing the canyon\nand picking up the same exit trail.</p>\n<h2 id=\"approach\">Approach</h2>\n<p>Utilize the free Zion Shuttle by parking at the Visitor's Center and\ntaking the shuttle to stop #6 The Grotto Trail. Follow signs/trail for\nAngels Landing. Approximately 1 mile in, the trail turns sharp left into\nthe narrows of Refrigerator canyon (denoted by the cooler temperatures).\nThe only and obvious footbridge on the trail marks the start of Lower\nRefrigerator.</p>\n<h2 id=\"descent\">Descent</h2>\n<p>From the footbridge, follow the canyon downstream down a short narrow\nsection of downclimbing that may be optionally rappelled depending on\ncomfort level by webbing found in a log jam.</p>\n<p>R1: 30' 2 bolted hangers LDC to a pool. The pool can be bypassed by\ncarefully traversing RDC above the waterline and jumping across to the\nlarge ledge. You are now out of the narrow section and at the top of the\nheadwall.</p>\n<p>R2: 115' 2 bolted hangers RDC to a small, 3-person ledge. Sequence\nthoughtfully for larger parties.</p>\n<p>R3: 190' 2 bolted hangers on the ledge. There are 4 total bolts and 3\nhangers, but 2 have eroded and are unfit for rappelling. Use the obvious\nchoice.</p>\n<h2 id=\"exit\">Exit</h2>\n<p>Follow the canyon RDC downstream through a short section of boulder\nhopping. When the debris begins to clear, look for a use trail RDC.\nFollow up to a grassy knoll and continue on the use trail to connect to\nthe main, paved, hiking trail.</p>\n<h2 id=\"red_tape\">Red tape</h2>\n<p>Zion canyoneering permit required. This permit is unavailable through\nthe online reservation system and must be obtained in person at the\npermit desk in the Visitor's Center.</p>\n<p>Be mindful of the shuttle time schedule and plan your day\naccordingly.</p>\n<h2 id=\"beta_sites\">Beta sites</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_en.png\" title=\"rwl_en.png\" alt=\"rwl_en.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://bluugnome.com/cyn_route/zion/zion_refrigerator-lower/zion_refrigerator_lower.aspx\">BluuGnome.com</a>\n: Refrigerator Canyon (Lower)</li>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_en.png\" title=\"rwl_en.png\" alt=\"rwl_en.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://canyoneeringusa.com/utah/zion/technical/lower-refrigerator-canyon\">CanyoneeringUSA.com</a>\n: Refrigerator</li>\n<li><img src=\"book.png\" title=\"book.png\" alt=\"book.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://ropewiki.com/User:Zion_Canyoneering_Book?id=Refrigerator_-_Lower\">Zion\nCanyoneering Book by Tom Jones</a> : Refrigerator - Lower</li>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_en.png\" title=\"rwl_en.png\" alt=\"rwl_en.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://zioncanyoneering.com/Canyon/Lower-Refrigerator-Canyon\">ZionCanyoneering.com</a>\n: Lower Refrigerator Canyon</li>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_en.png\" title=\"rwl_en.png\" alt=\"rwl_en.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://roadtripryan.com/go/t/utah/zion/refrigerator-canyon\">RoadTripRyan.com</a>\n: Refrigerator Canyon</li>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_en.png\" title=\"rwl_en.png\" alt=\"rwl_en.png\" /><a\nhref=\"https://thatadventurelife.com/2022/09/14/canyoneering-lower-refrigerator-canyon-zion-national-park/\">That\nAdventure Life</a> : Refrigerator Canyon</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media</h2>\n<p>Video from June 18, 2022 <a\nhref=\"https://youtu.be/lMyIYz9RVRw\">https://youtu.be/lMyIYz9RVRw</a></p>\n<p>{{#ev:vimeo|100067341}}</p>\n<h2 id=\"background\">Background</h2>\n",
